  "description": "The Fair Work Commission is Australia's national workplace relations tribunal. It is an independent body with the power to carry out a range of functions including:<br />\n<br />\n- Providing a safety new of minimum conditions, including minimum wages in awards;<br />\n- Facilitating good faith bargaining and the making of enterprise agreements;<br />\n- Granting remedies for unfair dismissal;                                                                                        <br />\n- Regulating the taking of industrial action; and<br />\n- Resolving a range of collective and individual workplace disputes.",
